{"node_id": "8ba719a615bb5689af28c50729484cb5", "title": "Slope from two points", "description": "Find the slope of the line that goes through the two points that are given to you.", "topic_path": ["Khan Academy (English - US curriculum)", "Math", "Get ready for Geometry", "Get ready for analytic geometry", "Slope", "Slope from two points"], "assessment_items": [{"item_id": "d0e4bdf38982543585699e8094266df8", "question_content": "**What is the slope of the line through $(1,0)$ and $(3,8)$?**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": ["$\\text{Slope}=\\dfrac{\\text{Rise}}{\\text{Run}}=\\dfrac{\\text{Change in }y}{\\text{Change in }x}$", "$\\begin{align}\n\\text{Slope}&=\\dfrac{8-0}{3-1}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{8}{2}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=4\n\\end{align}$", "The slope is $4$."], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "$4$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$\\dfrac14$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$-4$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$-\\dfrac14$", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "c7b8246e24cd5c3aa5c009ba7f5b0b91", "question_content": "**What is the slope of the line through $(-1,-7)$ and $(3,9)$?**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": ["$\\text{Slope}=\\dfrac{\\text{Rise}}{\\text{Run}}=\\dfrac{\\text{Change in }y}{\\text{Change in }x}$", "$\\begin{align}\n\\text{Slope}&=\\dfrac{9-(-7)}{3-(-1)}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{16}{4}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=4\n\\end{align}$\n", "The slope is $4$."], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "$4$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$\\dfrac14$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$-4$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$-\\dfrac14$", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "31dd853e106e5120b5ec404f52779097", "question_content": "**What is the slope of the line through $(-7,-2)$ and $(-6,7)$?**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": ["$\\text{Slope}=\\dfrac{\\text{Rise}}{\\text{Run}}=\\dfrac{\\text{Change in }y}{\\text{Change in }x}$", "$\\begin{align}\n\\text{Slope}&=\\dfrac{7-(-2)}{-6-(-7)}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{9}{1}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=9\n\\end{align}$\n", "The slope is $9$."], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "$9$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$\\dfrac19$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$-9$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$-\\dfrac19$", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "8b8907c769ea55b3a43ead4924267b2b", "question_content": "**What is the slope of the line through $(-2,-6)$ and $(2,2)$?**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": ["$\\text{Slope}=\\dfrac{\\text{Rise}}{\\text{Run}}=\\dfrac{\\text{Change in }y}{\\text{Change in }x}$", "$\\begin{align}\n\\text{Slope}&=\\dfrac{2-(-6)}{2-(-2)}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{8}{4}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=2\n\\end{align}$\n", "The slope is $2$."], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "$2$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$\\dfrac12$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$-2$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$-\\dfrac12$", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "7dc1baf4f4f458d9964e07ceaad8bad0", "question_content": "**What is the slope of the line through $(-1,8)$ and $(3,-4)$?**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": ["$\\text{Slope}=\\dfrac{\\text{Rise}}{\\text{Run}}=\\dfrac{\\text{Change in }y}{\\text{Change in }x}$", "$\\begin{align}\n\\text{Slope}&=\\dfrac{-4-8}{3-(-1)}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{-12}{4}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-3\n\\end{align}$\n", "The slope is $-3$."], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "$-3$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$-\\dfrac13$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$3$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$\\dfrac13$", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "11f4222a175e5cb9b79a1319d92bebd4", "question_content": "**What is the slope of the line through $(6,9)$ and $(7,1)$?**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": ["$\\text{Slope}=\\dfrac{\\text{Rise}}{\\text{Run}}=\\dfrac{\\text{Change in }y}{\\text{Change in }x}$", "$\\begin{align}\n\\text{Slope}&=\\dfrac{1-9}{7-6}\n\\\